    <forecast>
        <area aac="SA_FA001" description="South Australia" type="region">
            <forecast-period start-time-local="2026-03-31T09:19:44+10:30" end-time-local="2026-03-31T09:19:44+10:30" start-time-utc="2026-03-30T22:49:44Z" end-time-utc="2026-03-30T22:49:44Z">
                <text type="warning_summary_footer">For latest warnings go to www.bom.gov.au, subscribe to RSS feeds, call 1300 659 210* or listen for warnings on relevant TV and radio broadcasts.</text>
                <text type="synoptic_situation">A high pressure system over the Tasman sea extends a weak ridge over SA. A trough over central WA extends over southwest SA, and is forecast to move across the west and south later Tuesday, pushing into the northeast of SA on Wednesday. Another high pressure system is expected to become established south of the Bight late in the week.</text>
                <text type="product_footer">* Calls to 1300 numbers cost around 27.5c incl. GST, higher from mobiles or public phones.</text>
            </forecast-period>
        </area>
        <area aac="SA_PW003" description="Kangaroo Island" type="public-district" parent-aac="SA_FA001">
            <forecast-period index="0" start-time-local="2026-03-31T00:00:00+10:30" end-time-local="2026-04-01T00:00:00+10:30" start-time-utc="2026-03-30T13:30:00Z" end-time-utc="2026-03-31T13:30:00Z">
                <text type="forecast">Becoming cloudy. High chance of showers, most likely in the evening. Winds northerly 25 to 40 km/h turning northwesterly 15 to 25 km/h in the evening. Daytime maximum temperatures in the mid to high 20s.</text>
                <text type="fire_danger">High</text>
                <text type="uv_alert">Sun protection 10:20am to 4:20pm, UV Index predicted to reach 7 [High]</text>
            </forecast-period>
            <forecast-period index="1" start-time-local="2026-04-01T00:00:00+10:30" end-time-local="2026-04-02T00:00:00+10:30" start-time-utc="2026-03-31T13:30:00Z" end-time-utc="2026-04-01T13:30:00Z">
                <text type="forecast">Partly cloudy. Slight chance of a shower in the early morning. Winds westerly 15 to 25 km/h becoming light in the evening. Overnight temperatures falling to around 14 with daytime temperatures reaching the low to mid 20s.</text>
            </forecast-period>
            <forecast-period index="2" start-time-local="2026-04-02T00:00:00+10:30" end-time-local="2026-04-03T00:00:00+10:30" start-time-utc="2026-04-01T13:30:00Z" end-time-utc="2026-04-02T13:30:00Z">
                <text type="forecast">Partly cloudy. The chance of morning fog. Slight chance of a shower. Light winds becoming west to southwesterly 15 to 20 km/h during the day then tending south to southwesterly 15 to 25 km/h during the afternoon. Overnight temperatures falling to around 11 with daytime temperatures reaching the low 20s.</text>
            </forecast-period>
            <forecast-period index="3" start-time-local="2026-04-03T00:00:00+10:30" end-time-local="2026-04-04T00:00:00+10:30" start-time-utc="2026-04-02T13:30:00Z" end-time-utc="2026-04-03T13:30:00Z">
                <text type="forecast">Cloudy. The chance of morning fog. Slight chance of a shower, most likely in the morning and afternoon. Winds southeasterly 20 to 30 km/h. Overnight temperatures falling to around 13 with daytime temperatures reaching around 20.</text>
            </forecast-period>
        </area>
